# Project Conventions

## AGPL-3.0 licence header
Every new Dart file must begin with:
```dart
// Copyright (C) 2026 Polymath
// SPDX-License-Identifier: AGPL-3.0-or-later
```
One blank line after the header before `import` statements.

## Commit message format
```
type(scope): short description in present tense

Optional body: what and why, not how. Wrap at 72 chars.
```
Types: `feat`, `fix`, `refactor`, `chore`, `docs`, `test`, `ci`, `perf`
Scope: feature area — `programmes`, `auth`, `saved`, `notifications`, `admin`, `ingestion`, `theme`, `router`, `deps`

Examples:
```
feat(programmes): add filter by stipend and remote flag
fix(auth): handle expired Supabase session on app resume
ci(ingestion): add Devpost RSS cron workflow
chore(deps): bump supabase_flutter to 2.8.0
docs(schema): add push_flavor column to users table
```

## Branch naming
`feature/<short-description>`
`fix/<short-description>`
`chore/<short-description>`
`ci/<short-description>`

## Dart naming
| Thing             | Convention     | Example                      |
|-------------------|----------------|------------------------------|
| Files             | `snake_case`   | `programme_card.dart`        |
| Classes/Enums     | `PascalCase`   | `ProgrammeType`              |
| Variables/methods | `camelCase`    | `fetchOpenProgrammes()`      |
| Constants         | `camelCase`    | `defaultNotificationDays`    |
| Private members   | `_camelCase`   | `_repository`                |
| Enum values       | `camelCase`    | `ProgrammeType.fellowship`   |

## pubspec.yaml
- Dependencies alphabetically sorted within each section.
- Caret ranges (`^x.y.z`) only — no exact pins, no `any`.
- Comment non-obvious packages:
  ```yaml
  riverpod_annotation: ^2.0.0  # required for @riverpod codegen
  ```

## TODO comments
Format: `// TODO(#issue): description` — never bare `// TODO`.
If no issue exists yet, create one first.

## No magic strings for Supabase table/column names

Use **both** type-safety layers:

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `table_names.dart` | `Tables` / `Cols` constants for `.from()` / `.eq()` query strings |
| `database_types.dart` | Generated row shapes and enums (`supabase gen types dart`) |

Never hardcode table or column names as raw strings in repositories.

```dart
// lib/src/core/supabase/table_names.dart
abstract class Tables {
  static const programmes     = 'programmes';
  static const tags           = 'tags';
  static const programmeTags  = 'programme_tags';
  static const users          = 'users';
  static const savedProgrammes = 'saved_programmes';
}
abstract class Cols {
  static const reviewed       = 'reviewed';
  static const closesAt       = 'closes_at';
  static const nigeriaEligible = 'nigeria_eligible';
  // ... add as needed
}
```
